Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.30,0:01:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect to be first.\NOther than getting one's affairs in order and simplifying life, for people who are increasingly
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.94,0:01:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing non-dual reality.\NYou're increasingly experiencing what?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.35,0:01:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-dual reality.\NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.35,0:01:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NNon-dual, non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.35,0:01:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-duality.\NOh, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.54,0:01:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got it.\NAnd therefore find relationships and work and life structures as you previously knew
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.10,0:01:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it relatively irrelevant.\NLess attractive, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.70,0:02:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What guidance can you provide?\NThe motivation has to shift from gain, huh, and the various things that ordinarily
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.63,0:02:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,steer people through the linear world, and in their place to take on the value of non-linear\Nvalues, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.81,0:02:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, to be of service to the world.\NSo you may hold the job out of gain, out of vanity for the title, out of desire, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.64,0:02:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you transcend that level.\NNow, of what meaning or significance is the same job.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.36,0:02:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It may transform in meaning, yeah.\NDid that answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.04,0:02:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you're serving a function for humanity and society, and that becomes\Nthe way you contextualize what you do, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.13,0:03:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,To be of service, then, no matter what you do, is really a being of service to life,\Nyou know, in all of its expressions and forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.87,0:03:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt takes 20 workmen to lift a tent for the circus, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.83,0:03:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Good question.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.83,0:03:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All in general, it has to do with Alzheimer's and that condition, and one has the experience\Nthat I've had a couple of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.83,0:03:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThis is a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.83,0:03:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The Alzheimer's is a very good one.\NWhat about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.83,0:03:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, patients that have Alzheimer's.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.17,0:03:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Alzheimer's, you know.\NAlzheimer's, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.17,0:03:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I never can say that right.\NIt's got a Z, a Z in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.17,0:03:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a Z.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.17,0:03:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnyway, patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.17,0:03:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What about it?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.17,0:03:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell them what is really happening with the soul, with people who have that disease?\NCan you tell who's happening with whose soul?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.55,0:03:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours or the patient's?\NNo, the patient's.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.55,0:03:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The patient's.\NOh, the patient's soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.55,0:03:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYeah, what's happening with the patient's soul is up to the patient and God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you want to know about it?\NWell, she must know they're in pain, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.55,0:04:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's simple.\NYou know, I was the only doctor in the county, and they would go to the nursing home and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,see the Alzheimer's patients.\NSo, I saw them all over the county, from Prescott on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.77,0:04:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still a lot of back talk in the background.\NI found that most of it, that the anguish was on the part of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.80,0:04:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The patient, I'd go to see them.\NThey'd say, oh, poor Aunt Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.96,0:04:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't remember who she is anymore, and this and that.\NAnd the family is all upset and wailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.96,0:04:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'd go see Aunt Granny.\NI'd say, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.96,0:04:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, fine.\NHow do you like this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.96,0:04:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's nice.\NOh, it's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.96,0:04:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How's the food?\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.96,0:04:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You got any complaints today?\NNo, no, no, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.14,0:05:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what day it is?\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.43,0:05:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You know how old you are?\NShe said, oh, I'm a lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.43,0:05:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a lady.\NI don't want to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.43,0:05:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, she doesn't remember how old she is, and who cares?\NSo, the subjective experiential of straightforward Alzheimer's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's senility, dimension, whatever you want to call it.\NThe main anguish is in the witness, because if you don't remember a lot of what went on,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.52,0:05:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,what difference does it make?\NAs it is, most people don't remember what went on in their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.25,0:05:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that?\NCan you give me a minute-by-minute, second-by-second recall, you know, of even one day in your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.25,0:05:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYou can remember a few highlights.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.25,0:05:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, what people mourn is really the vanity of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the vanity of it.\NI remember I saw my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.18,0:06:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She was 99.\NAnd I went to see her, and she says, oh, you're from New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.94,0:06:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NI said, my grandson is a doctor in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.97,0:06:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, yes, Granny.\NAnd then I began to talk about who I was and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.10,0:06:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden, she said, all of a sudden, she started to cry.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.10,0:06:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, would you say there's no difference, then, between a gastrointestinal trance disorder or Alzheimer's?\NStraight Alzheimer's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.10,0:06:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, then there's Alzheimer's would disturb the emotionality and all, but that's irrelevant to the Alzheimer's,\Nbecause lots of people at the same age without Alzheimer's get the same thing, depression or agitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.10,0:07:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you treat the negative symptoms.\NBut Alzheimer's itself, I always felt as though the spirit has already left the body progressively, and there's very little left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.10,0:07:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, Bill Wilson, who was the founder of AA, and I knew him for years before he died, and I was one of the doctors who used to see him.\NAnd he would lapse periodically.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.20,0:07:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And he would say, he visited different realms of heaven, you know.\NHe would go into it like a lapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.20,0:07:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And he would say, it is true.\NThere are many mansions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many mansions on my father's side, you know.\NSo, that there is, what he was saying, which we recently discovered with kinesiology, is that there are multiple heavens, multiple ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.20,0:07:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, as a clinician, in dealing with Alzheimer's, what is your recommendation?\NMake sure they have breakfast and lunch and dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.41,0:08:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NGot enough socks for the week, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.04,0:08:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.\NYou're bringing in books from another line here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.17,0:08:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.17,0:08:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That answers the mystery.\NHe'll just sign in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.17,0:08:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't need it.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.17,0:08:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal inscriptions.\NThat's all I can do to get him to sign his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.36,0:08:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI did put it with best regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.36,0:08:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NHe did.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.36,0:08:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky.\NHe usually doesn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.36,0:08:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOn the one hand, one wants to serve the higher good without considering gain and loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.36,0:08:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NBut, on the other hand, one wants to live in abundance rather than in poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.36,0:08:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you reconcile those two?\NWhat have you got against poverty?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.84,0:08:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it just feels nicer to have, you know, a credit card, be able to take an airplane.\NThat's not poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.84,0:08:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's lack of wealth, right?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty is something else.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.07,0:08:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Lack of wealth.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.26,0:08:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's a very common problem.\NProbably one of the most common problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.26,0:08:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.26,0:08:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.26,0:08:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.88,0:08:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.58,0:08:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.58,0:08:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.58,0:09:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.19,0:09:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.19,0:09:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.19,0:09:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.32,0:09:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.32,0:09:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's probably the most common.\NSure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.32,0:09:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You become, you fulfill your own potential to the greatest degree you can fulfill it.\NAnd the consequences are automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.57,0:09:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you need to do to make it happen.\NBecause, because of the consequence of that which you are, you draw to yourself by attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.02,0:09:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that which will elude you if you seek it out of.\NThe gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.40,0:09:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The negativity.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.40,0:10:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, one should learn to enjoy what the world would call poverty.\NThe simplicity of it, the lack of demand of it, I mean what you need in the refrigerator
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.04,0:10:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is a six pack of Pepsi and a piece of cheese, what else do you want?\NI lived that way for years, and in those days I used to truck manure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.24,0:10:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When I left the world, I left a grand lifestyle, more grand than you can even imagine.\NI mean it was grand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.89,0:10:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The club I belonged to was so exclusive, nobody knows the name of it to this day, but they\Nwere the heads of all the great sources of wealth in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.13,0:10:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I just put my tools in the back of the truck and drove away.\NIt was great.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.12,0:11:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Free as a bird, free, free.\NI had to drive down the highway with a load of manure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.31,0:11:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it for ten bucks, so they're the big dairy farm in McGuireville, and for ten bucks\Nthey'd load up the back of the truck and I would truck it all the way to Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.34,0:11:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the manure baron of Sedona.\NI controlled the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.12,0:11:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody wanted to get their truck.\NPick up ten bucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.42,0:11:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Truck 30 with manure, so anyway, so I would sell it for 40 or 45, so I bought it for ten,\Nsold it for 45, and to do that I only had to drive eight miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.33,0:11:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you can't beat that.\NAnd I was free as a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.55,0:11:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I could do it when I wanted to do it, not do it when I wanted to do it.\NIf I didn't need money, heck with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.13,0:11:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you.\NI lived that way for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.05,0:11:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Only reluctantly was forced to give it up, to tell you the truth.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:12:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you enjoy simplicity, so don't see it as poverty, see it as simplicity.\NAnd this period of simplicity is a gift, and when you've extracted all there is to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.54,0:12:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,from that, that learning phase goes over.\NYou may then have to learn how to be the responsible steward of abundance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.78,0:12:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be sorry you weren't the poor again, I'll tell you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.18,0:12:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, I'm Grant.\NMy name is Grant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.41,0:12:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.91,0:12:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is John.\NI'm honored and also a little bit intimidated being up here, so if my question doesn't make
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.91,0:12:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,any sense, just re-ask it.\NIt doesn't have to make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.91,0:12:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.91,0:12:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What you said earlier this morning about meditation, my spiritual ego felt a little\Ndisparaged by that, an avid practicer of meditation myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.14,0:12:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then with further reflection, what I got from what you said was that if all you did\Nwas meditate, then that would mean nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.54,0:13:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If it didn't translate in some change of behavior, some way of perceiving things, responding to\Nthings, then it would mean nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.54,0:13:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And in my sense of it is that it has helped me create a sense of equanimity about the\Ncoming and going of things, processes in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.08,0:13:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So I myself have found it very beneficial.\NI did it for 20 years, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.08,0:13:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd so the second part of my question was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.08,0:13:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't exactly a fizzle, though.\NIn your comments about it, it was somewhat negativistic about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.08,0:13:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I was wondering, did I perceive what you said upon further reflection to be more\Naccurate of what you were trying to say, to how would you say that the 20 years of meditating
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.40,0:13:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,two hours a day, did that have anything to do with how you are now?\NIt would be hard to say, because you see, it's the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.20,0:14:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention with which you meditate, pray, walk the maze, asceticism, I also did asceticism,\Nand left my own devices, I'd weigh about 90, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.62,0:14:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So asceticism can become a way of life.\NCertain things are realized, I'm certain, as a result of the meditative state itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.51,0:14:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm saying is how well does it transpose?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.51,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You meditate for an hour and you gain some interest.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You have interesting insights.\NAnd then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.69,0:14:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to me, it gives me practice at being in the audience looking at the movie, as opposed\Nto the actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.83,0:14:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes you into the field.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.18,0:14:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, what you want to do, maybe I didn't make it clear, is translate what you saw from\Nmeditation into contemplation so it becomes what you are in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.18,0:14:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo I think that kind of augments that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.18,0:15:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of a laboratory.\NWell, also meditation trains you in one-pointedness of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.18,0:15:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that one-pointedness of mind later comes on usefully in other spiritual practices.\NBecause when you decide to make what I call the final run, when you decide to make the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,final run, you're going to be walking the edge of the razor.\NYou're going to walk the edge of the razor and stay on the edge of the razor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.62,0:15:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And you need that disciplined one-pointedness of mind to see the crest of each experience\Narising and to release it as it arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.62,0:15:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And not to anticipate jumping to the front of the wave of experience, which is control\Nand also fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor is it hanging to the back of the wave, which is clinging to the past.\NSo to be on the wave of the presence of now is an expertise that can be learned in meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.62,0:15:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThen applied in the style of contemplation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.17,0:16:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So contemplation is a way of being meditative about life and the past.\NAbout life as you walk through life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.58,0:16:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's only an artificial disparity.\NWhat I was trying to point out is a lot of times people isolate that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.42,0:16:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I meditate from here to there.\NThen I'm who I always was until four.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.42,0:16:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I meditate from five to six.\NIt tends to get compartmentalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.42,0:16:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NSo if you don't change what you're doing, you're going to keep getting what you're getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.42,0:16:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo to apply that which you see to the way you are in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.48,0:16:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the contemplation.\NAnd then it's the all-day fulfillment of what you've achieved within meditation, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.48,0:16:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd in your third book, you talk about meditating in context rather than the content of a mantra or following the breath and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.67,0:17:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Where, without going into that, I don't mean to Bogart that.\NNo, each of these spiritual practices is befitting a certain level of the progression of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.67,0:17:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are things that are useful at this level.\NThey're hanging to the past at this level.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.67,0:17:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's things that will take you from this level to the next level.\NSo there's a time to walk the maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.67,0:17:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a time to do the rosary.\NThere's a time to do sackcloth and ashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.67,0:17:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a time to do asceticism.\NThere's a time to do selfless service.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.67,0:17:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not a linear logical progression.\NSo something may be of need and appeal to you at a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.74,0:17:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd at other times, it could be an evasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.83,0:17:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is a spiritual, beneficial practice here could be an evasion here, see?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.83,0:17:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.83,0:17:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NGood question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.83,0:17:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat'd be a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.55,0:17:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.16,0:18:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I just want to thank you for coming back into our world and writing those three incredible books.\NAnd it seems like it must have taken an awful lot of effort because, you know, we're all in this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.28,0:18:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.28,0:18:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just, when I see you speaking and you seem to recall some of that time in your life before you came back, it seems like you really start to bliss out.\NAnd you could just go out there and just stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.28,0:18:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really appreciate you coming back and helping the rest of us.\NYou can't really talk about those states when they begin to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.00,0:18:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NI see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.00,0:18:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you've got to draw back into, again, to the personage, you know.\NAnd I remind myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.00,0:18:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the communicative transmitter of communication.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.51,0:18:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And besides, there's plenty of time on the other side.\NForever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.50,0:18:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's a while.\NYou've got forever when you get there, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.63,0:19:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my question is.\NYou've got to do what you've got to do while you're down there, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.63,0:19:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Father.\NMy question is, I'm doing the lessons in the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.63,0:19:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I haven't read the text.\NI haven't read the text deliberately because of what you said about how it demonizes the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.63,0:19:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you watch for the demonization of the ego, you'll see it there.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.63,0:19:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's a mistake to set up a duality within yourself already, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.86,0:19:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So is it worthwhile to read the text?\NOr are you better off reading Huang Po or Maharachi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.86,0:19:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it worth reading the text, I guess, is my point?\NI'd have to reread it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.86,0:19:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been many a year.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.86,0:19:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's interesting.\NIt's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't fall in.\NJust be aware of the demonization.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.86,0:19:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just watch that downside.\NThat downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.86,0:19:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,See, once you've heard the truth, anything that's in error in what you read will stand\Nout of its own, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.95,0:19:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll say, well, that's demonizing the ego.\NYeah, you know, it shrieks and claws at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.95,0:20:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is, it's also true from a certain other level of abstraction.\NThe ego is the dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.95,0:20:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the Komodo dragon.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.95,0:20:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will, frankly, throw you over the cliff to survive.\NRather than surrender, it'll throw you over the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.95,0:20:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll kill you over and over again.\NI think I'll stay away from the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.95,0:20:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to demonize the text.\NI'm just saying there is a fault in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.95,0:20:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do the workbook.\NWell, you see, the textbook does calibrate 50 points lower than the workbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.95,0:20:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is reflected there.\NAnd it sort of stands out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.95,0:20:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've heard the truth, you say, well, the interpreter, the translator maybe just\Ntranslated it incorrectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.02,0:20:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A man shrieks and claws at you in quotes.\NAnd it's not really doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.02,0:20:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But you perceive it as that.\NSo a clarification of that I think would help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.02,0:21:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I had to rewrite that paragraph, I'd say you perceive it as shrieking and clawing\Nat you, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.02,0:21:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's not.\NIt's your projection.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.02,0:21:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you're seeing the ego.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.02,0:21:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I also heard something about a group OM.\NI was wondering if we could maybe do that before we leave today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Edward, you said you were going to hear OM?\NI didn't say anything about having an OM.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.11,0:21:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you did.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.21,0:21:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she did.\NDidn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.21,0:21:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI didn't say anything about an OM.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.21,0:21:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI was going to say MO, and I got it backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.24,0:21:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't say MO.\NWe met.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.24,0:21:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We met.\NOh, no, home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.24,0:21:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I said we'd go home at 5.\NHello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.24,0:21:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Phyllis Hartzler.\NI'm from Pennsylvania.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.33,0:21:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just wanted to thank you.\NI don't really have a question that I can think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.66,0:21:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll be quick.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.66,0:21:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.66,0:21:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.66,0:21:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what's the time?\NDo we have time on the line?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.66,0:21:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NMy name's Locke, and I just live down the road in Cornville.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.66,0:22:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice to meet you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.66,0:22:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.42,0:22:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.96,0:22:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.66,0:22:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.66,0:22:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.66,0:22:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.66,0:22:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's nice to meet you.\NYou live in Cornville?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.64,0:22:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOh, lucky man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.64,0:22:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Good karma, huh?\NIt's nice out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.64,0:22:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I live at .\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.09,0:22:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You said something during the lecture about a bomb killing so many people and, so, what?\NNot having a judgment about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.34,0:22:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember in a previous lifetime I was a young pastor for a particular church, and\NI was talking to this older pastor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.67,0:23:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and a bird flew and hit the window and fell down into the bushes and he just\Ncalmly he calmly got up and got the bird and held on to it until it woke up and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.78,0:23:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,took off and I remember thinking I don't know I don't know shit about compassion\Nand and and and I guess my question is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.27,0:23:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you know how you know I mean I mean my my I was like so what so you know I've\Nseen birds hit the window all the time so but I think that so what that I was
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.83,0:23:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,having at that time is different than the so what that you're talking about\Nand I'm wondering if you could just sort of you know how can I be compassionate
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.35,0:23:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,without making a judgment about something how can you avoid making a\Njudgment
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.05,0:23:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nwell you just become compassionate towards all of life in all of its
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.99,0:24:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions whether it's a busload of children being blown up or a bird\Nhitting the window you see that that is the interaction that's the way creation
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.79,0:24:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,unfolds and that's the karma of each entity you know physicality and the\Ntemporality that goes with physicality that's one reason enlightenment is to go
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.49,0:24:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond that physicality and so that you're not run over on the road anymore\Nsee that bird had really good karma
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.91,0:24:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that picked him up sure yeah really good karma and and and and the I mean I mean\NI did the minister and you go oh my god I can't believe this cruel world and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.63,0:24:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,birds hit the window oh yeah like that it was sort of like he just he just knew\Nwhat needed to be done he wasn't oh yeah judgmental place well no that's because
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.01,0:24:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the way you are that's the way you are you cherish all of life in all of its\Nexpressions and that's the way you are you cherish all of life in all of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.29,0:25:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it could be flowers it can be the bird you know compassion for all of\Nlife in all its expressions it's just a way of being with the world you know
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.64,0:25:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you already appreciate that so that means you're already that way yourself\Notherwise you wouldn't have been impressed by what he did yes my name is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.77,0:25:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jackie I'm from California I read your books in the end of last year and came\Nto my first seminar in December went home and all
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.43,0:25:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven or hell broke loose big time yes I remember you saying that from the\NDecember seminar two things I took home with me whatever isn't integrous in your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.15,0:25:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,life in all areas in whatever area yeah would fall by the wayside the world\Ncomes will show up yeah and and whatever happens just say so what I've been saying
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.27,0:26:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so many times I've been saying so many times I've been saying so many times I've been saying so many times I've been saying so many times\Nso what every day you know I I'm an RN I had my own practice I closed that due
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.07,0:26:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to other situations my husband had had an alcoholic problem for a long time and\NI had told him he needs to do something about this or I was going to walk away
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.61,0:26:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because I I felt it was infringing on even my health and my stress from it so\Nhe said fine I'm going to do something about this because I felt it was
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.59,0:26:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,infringing on even my stress from it so I felt it was infringing on even my stress from it so I thought hey he went to a hey\NI'll go to a hey he went to he stayed sober for a week came home and told me
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.73,0:27:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,her lectures can be helped by the\Ncurrent marriage girl
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.46,0:27:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this Oh I love\NOkay, the prayer of permission to be released from the relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.02,0:27:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if the alcoholism couldn't be brought under control.\NI didn't expect the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.72,0:27:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I had prayed a prayer similar to what you had said to pray,\Nwhich was the third thing I took home,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.92,0:27:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is whatever time I have left, I dedicate it all to your service.\NOkay, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.24,0:28:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever's left.\NIf I die tonight, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.28,0:28:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,C'est la vie.\NAnd that's when everything hit the fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.26,0:28:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What's next?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.25,0:28:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You can talk then.\NCan you talk then?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.41,0:28:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm at a loss to even know what's going to be next.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.92,0:28:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NYou don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.39,0:28:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You still don't know what it means.\NYou still don't know what it means to not.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.15,0:28:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You still don't know what it means to not resist it and to not seek it,\Nto be neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.65,0:28:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right.\NSo what is that neutral?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.69,0:28:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If it happens, it happens.\NIf it doesn't happen, it doesn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.19,0:28:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's okay that it's happened.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.75,0:28:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't throw you about in the boat, see?\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.05,0:28:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've maintained a certain equilibrium\Nat things that would throw in a lot of people themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.05,0:29:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd now you're somehow liberated,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.77,0:29:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so you've got some kind of a freedom.\NI'm free as a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.95,0:29:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're free as a bird.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.15,0:29:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're free as a bird,\Nand now you just maintain your spiritual balance,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.23,0:29:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is ready for you will come upon you as the next hello,\Nyou know, like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.41,0:29:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NAnd you just keep going along with it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.44,0:29:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.88,0:29:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I can do.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.08,0:29:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a plan somewhere.\NI have to somehow believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.64,0:29:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a plan somewhere in the confusion,\Nbecause it wouldn't have blown up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.38,0:29:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt must be a set trigger,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.18,0:29:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're taking a jump in consciousness that released it,\Nso that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.84,0:30:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's very interesting.\NWe look forward to the next installment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.41,0:30:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe she should only come to every other lecture, okay?\NYou're speaking to both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.10,0:30:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NDo you want me to stand in front of this here?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.20,0:30:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWait, that won't go too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.95,0:30:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNo, I'll stand here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.67,0:30:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't recognize that.\NIs that something I wrote?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.09,0:30:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.57,0:30:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NAmazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.98,0:30:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, wait.\NHe has a question he wants to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.54,0:30:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.24,0:30:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My question, you mentioned today\Nthat we have a responsibility to respect our assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.90,0:30:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A responsibility, what?\NTo respect the assets that we are given,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.12,0:30:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to be stewards to our assets.\NYes, that's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.38,0:30:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHow does one reconcile, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.58,0:30:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if your asset,\Nis in the business world,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.28,0:31:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and your intention is enlightenment,\Nhowever it comes,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.42,0:31:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you reconcile\Nhaving a sense of responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.40,0:31:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to participate in daily life,\Nactivating your assets in the business world,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.72,0:31:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet at the same time,\Nreach a state of enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.56,0:31:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which could render you completely unable\Nto fulfill those assets?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.88,0:31:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.94,0:31:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo it's a matter of attachment
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.16,0:31:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way in which you contextualize its value.\NI mean, you've got to do something with your body
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.53,0:31:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,while you hang out waiting to be enlightened,\Nyou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.41,0:31:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And you might as well be using it for the good of mankind,\Nwhether it's producing a product.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.55,0:31:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, I need a pen to sign things with.\NSomebody's got to make the pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.71,0:31:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's got to ship it.\NIt has to be boxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.39,0:31:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, the qualities of human life are multiple.\NSo we serve each other in multiple ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.03,0:32:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple ways.\NSo I say if you're in business,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.42,0:32:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then see what that value is to the world,\Nthe employee to the employees
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.32,0:32:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as the source of employment, et cetera.\NSo it serves multiple functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.97,0:32:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you see its intrinsic value,\Nyou have to,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.91,0:32:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you're neither attracted\Nnor do you have an aversion to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.81,0:32:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just what,\Nthen after a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.19,0:32:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you stop identifying,\Nyou're identifying with the body
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.09,0:32:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see that's a phenomena.\NIt's a phenomena of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.87,0:32:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't need a personal you to make it happen.\NYou may have initiated it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.13,0:32:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but now it's going to have like a life\Nor an energy of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.89,0:32:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to which you have a certain responsibility.\NNow, the degree of involvement is something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.07,0:32:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So responsibility is one thing.\NInvolvement is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.65,0:32:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can find somebody to run the factory\Nwhile you join an ashram,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.63,0:32:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so why?\NSo why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.38,0:32:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.02,0:33:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't find somebody to run the factory\Nand they're all going to lose their jobs
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.24,0:33:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the factory's going to close\Nand the townspeople are going to go poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.98,0:33:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to hold you in there\Nuntil you find somebody, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.59,0:33:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that can hold it together\Nfor the sake of the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.48,0:33:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you've activated that energy\Nand then you are, in effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.86,0:33:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,neutral to it,\Nyou can then go on your own personal path
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.68,0:33:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that that asset of yours\Nis alive and has its own momentum.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.30,0:33:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so you try to find\Nsomebody that will fulfill that function for you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.54,0:33:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby free yourself, huh?\NYou know, I was chief of staff
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.36,0:33:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,at Girls Ranch there in Prescott\Nfor many years
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.20,0:33:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because there wasn't any doctor around.\NWell, how am I going to get out of there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.84,0:33:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no other doctor around,\Nyou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.40,0:33:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're like hooked\Nuntil you find somebody that could take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.28,0:33:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same with the nursing homes, you know,\Nuntil finally the county could find somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.50,0:33:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So you sort of stayed out of a sense of responsibility\Nand obligation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.66,0:34:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, eventually, you get released from it.\NYou get too old to do it, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.92,0:34:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Age releases you at the end, thank goodness.\NYou may be ready to quit,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.00,0:34:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but the old reaper is going to take you out of it.\NThank you, reaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.63,0:34:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a good friend of the reaper,\Njust when you need him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.36,0:34:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, baby.\NHooked you out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.90,0:34:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NHi, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.30,0:34:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Beverly from Dallas.\NWe found your books this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.35,0:34:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And we watched your videos all for last year.\NAnd I'm just so appreciative for what you've done
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.23,0:34:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and for God giving me, you know, this chance again.\NAnd so my question, I really formed at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.61,0:34:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, well, I want to get a question\Nso I can talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.65,0:34:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And...\NAnd...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.91,0:35:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So my question, and I don't really care\Nwhether it's right or wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.88,0:35:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but can you reach enlightenment reading your books?\NHmm, interesting question.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.66,0:35:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I would presume that putting it into practice\Nis what makes the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.31,0:35:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,However, even to have heard of it already changes you.\NYou know, even the Buddha said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.27,0:35:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Rare is it to be a human being.\NExtremely rare in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.09,0:35:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarer still.\NRarer still is it to have heard of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.07,0:35:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And rarest of all is having heard of it to pursue it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.94,0:35:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's a great gift to be a human being.\NIt's a great gift to even hear of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.90,0:35:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's certainly a great gift to be attracted to it.\NYou know, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.00,0:35:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortunate, karmically fortunate are we\Nthat we've even heard of it and esteemed it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.46,0:35:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or respected, you know.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.92,0:36:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When you start carrying around,\Nyou know, Huang Po under your arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.96,0:36:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you're getting there.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.28,0:36:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't read that yet, but we've got it.\NHuang Po or the aphorisms of, et cetera, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.83,0:36:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They became enlightened in a different culture\Nand they expressed it in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.55,0:36:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And, but they become respected, you know,\Nancestors respected, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.79,0:36:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I didn't want to cry because my husband is here\Nand we want to get a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.57,0:36:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can.\NAnd he's got a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.49,0:36:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a dollar.\NI don't either.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.33,0:36:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm resigning the dollar fee.\NWell, no one else, you have to tell the story
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.57,0:36:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because nobody else is going to buy it.\NI won't tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.93,0:36:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I got it.\NWe put it in the dollar bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.93,0:36:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.58,0:36:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell everyone the story.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.40,0:36:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI can't tell you the whole story now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.44,0:36:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NIt was in the Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.50,0:36:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it was in the Alps.\NNo, it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.80,0:36:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in the Himalayas.\NNo, it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.14,0:37:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No other freaking place.\NMachu Picchu.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.14,0:37:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NPeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.96,0:37:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The Andes.\NThe high up in the Andes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.18,0:37:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The Andes in Peru are just mysterious.\NI mean, just wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.55,0:37:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And Machu Picchu, of course, is impressive.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.99,0:37:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NMy name's Mike and I'm from Dallas.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.29,0:37:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And that beautiful spirit has been in my life for 40 years.\NSo we share a lot in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.88,0:37:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to also thank you and express our gratitude\Nfor what you...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.94,0:37:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.46,0:37:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou've meant to us as you've been in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.52,0:37:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The question I have is some clarification\Nin regards to causality versus intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.26,0:37:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Or causality and intention.\NI've heard you say that when you snip the apple,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.81,0:37:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't cause it to drop.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.57,0:37:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The field did.\NThe gravity did.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.77,0:38:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Gravity did, yeah.\NAnd then you've also said that when you have...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.23,0:38:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,With the Empire State Bill,\Nthat there was a an intention that went in there and into the field of an
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.69,0:38:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite potentiality yeah right so my question is could the snipping of the\NApple be the intention in the infinite field of potentiality that yeah brings
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.58,0:38:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the actualization of the intention well it was you see potentiality becomes\Nactuality when conditions are favorable oh so it's favorable because all you do
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.13,0:38:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not going to cause the Apple to fall you're going to just change the\Ntiming of it because come foot you know in autumn it's going to drop of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.55,0:39:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so you're just trying to jump it up so\Nintentionality then becomes potentiality when the conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.75,0:39:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to\Nfacilitate that actuality are present so it doesn't like otherwise you would have
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.85,0:39:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,life going against itself you know I'm saying linear life at least going\Nagainst itself so the potentiality then is extremely powerful powerful you might
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.52,0:39:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,say all of creation is the actualization of the potentiality of the will of God\Nwho only had to say yes to the spark and foreverness evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.16,0:39:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,within the third three dimensional world okay a follow-up question is it\Nseemed like when you've talked about the lower levels of consciousness that that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.48,0:40:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a big attractor field and they get more of what were they're resonating\Nfor their realizing isn't theontology I guess with the intention is it in Jagl
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.98,0:40:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Arif this kind of thing or is there a but Minute\Nlevel consciousness and then the togetherness of the consciousness I can
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.66,0:40:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality is\Npotentiated at that point
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.83,0:40:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,at a higher level of consciousness?\NYes, because you contextualize the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.79,0:40:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,different, your intention is different.\NSo I say the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.99,0:40:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you should prepare for enlightenment\Nis because
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.71,0:40:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody here is already committed to it,\Naligned with it, they're studying
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.15,0:40:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it, practicing it, well, the end is\Nuncertain, unless you do something
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.13,0:40:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to make it, you know,\Nto refuse it. It's going to constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.03,0:40:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,unfold to you.\NAnd whatever the way that you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.11,0:40:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,need to see to go, it's going to be like\Nsuddenly illuminated, you suddenly see this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.15,0:40:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,pathway over here, and if you hadn't\Nchosen enlightenment, you wouldn't see that pathway
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.09,0:40:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,over there. So\Nthose things are not definable,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.92,0:40:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but you've obviously\Nchanged the course
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.30,0:41:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of events, yeah?\NOkay, very good, thanks again.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.26,0:41:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Dallas, eh?\NHere?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.37,0:41:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all in this.\NThe chair is like right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.45,0:41:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but the box is pointing\Ndifferent. Well, I moved in because
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.40,0:41:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody was sitting in the room. It's hard for them to get\Nin and out, but the chair is out that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.05,0:41:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDr. Hawkins, I have
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.52,0:41:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoyed your chanting Aum\Nwhen you have done so in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.28,0:41:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With your permission, may we have quiet\Nfrom the audience, and would you give us
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.40,0:41:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as comfortable as you can\Na nice, long, and deep
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.20,0:41:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Aum, also for the purpose\Nfor those who purchase a tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.46,0:41:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can listen to your Aum\Nat the end of the seminar later.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.46,0:42:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We can listen to your Aum\Nto our hearts content.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.96,0:42:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You told us that you aren't allowed to do the octopus\Nanymore, so
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.96,0:42:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,my friends and I would like to give you this.\NOh, isn't that adorable?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.65,0:42:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. My friends have the questions.\NI don't have a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.65,0:42:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThat's an adorable octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.65,0:42:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always admired them.\NIncredible entity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.18,0:42:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look at the eyes here.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.18,0:43:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nmy question is in regards to assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.84,0:43:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it important\Nto know your assets?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.16,0:43:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm wondering,\Nis mediocrity an asset?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.16,0:43:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great\Nliberation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.90,0:43:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a virtuoso, an expert,\Nuh,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.60,0:43:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite a pressure, isn't it?\NTo be a world champion chess player once,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.44,0:43:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,your life is screwed, you know?\NEspecially if you're beat by
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.44,0:43:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Blue. Oh, boy.\NYour life is hell, thenceforth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.14,0:43:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, no, mediocrity\Nis a way of being sort of at
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.26,0:43:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,neutral. And I think\Nsometimes the spirit, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.39,0:43:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,takes sort of a rest\Nand goes on vacation for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.39,0:44:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I think this one,\Nyou know, when I just have a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.48,0:44:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,easy life, have a good family,\Na good job, and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.48,0:44:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,let it be at that and learn to enjoy\Nwhat you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.48,0:44:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to enjoy that which\Nyou are may be the lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.48,0:44:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To appreciate and see the\Nvalue of enjoying of being nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.48,0:44:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you,\Nbeing nobody is wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.85,0:44:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to being somebody,\Nit has a great payoff, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.85,0:44:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're driving down the road\Nin the truck and nobody knows you from Adam,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.85,0:44:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're not\Nbeholden to anybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.27,0:44:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to be anywhere, don't have to sign anything,\Ndon't have to vote on anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.27,0:44:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to be quoted, don't have to appear\Non television or radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.16,0:44:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a free bird. Are you letting anybody\Ndown by doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.16,0:44:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course, the word needs you to save them,\Nbut it'll do without you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.16,0:45:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I mean, if you, like you talked about\Nbeing responsible for your
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.16,0:45:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,assets, right? Well, yes.\NWhat is your asset? So, your asset is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.16,0:45:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the learning of the value\Nof just being ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.16,0:45:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's learning\Nto live without specialness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.16,0:45:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the ego wants specialness.\NAnd it wants specialness of relationships
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.26,0:45:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and goods and values\Nand titles and recognitions and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.26,0:45:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it wants to voice its opinion about\Neverything.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.52,0:45:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to learn to live\Nin that space is extremely valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.77,0:45:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can be with God\Nthere. You just be with it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.43,0:45:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,there. Thank you.\NAny progressive demands will appear
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.86,0:45:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,only too soon.\NThe next emotional
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.87,0:45:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,tsunami. Thank you both\Nfor being here today. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.41,0:45:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question.\NWhen you talked about working with the girls
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.41,0:46:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at the ranch,\Nwhen we work with people that are
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.86,0:46:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at these levels, I see today\Nthat you have amusements. You can say,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.86,0:46:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you can laugh at people in\Nthe below 200 non-integrist
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.86,0:46:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,levels.\NBut some of us in the trenches, it's hard
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.86,0:46:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to maintain\Na sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.47,0:46:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,humor.\NIt's hard to continue in a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.47,0:46:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,positive space when\Nyou're working with a lot, especially
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.47,0:46:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,people in alcoholism.\NWell, and some don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.47,0:46:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have tools\Nin that area? Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.94,0:46:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,professional detachment is something\Nyou learn. And eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.94,0:46:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you learn compassion without attachment.\NAnd attachment
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.94,0:46:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is trying to exert your will on\Noutcomes. So
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.16,0:46:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you learn to serve\Nwhatever you can serve, because
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.16,0:46:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it's your\Nturn to hold their hand, but you're
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.16,0:47:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,not the last one in line.\NAnd they'll be going down to the next hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.16,0:47:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NSo you serve your function to the best of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.16,0:47:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,your ability, and\Nyou convey the message. You can carry
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.16,0:47:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the message, you can't carry the person.\NOnce you convey the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.35,0:47:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,options, and many people\Nwill choose the negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.47,0:47:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,many people would rather die\Nthan give in. You know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.47,0:47:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell them, you get behind the car\None more time, they're gonna
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.97,0:47:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,put you away for\Nfive years. What do you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.58,0:47:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,think the first thing you did when you got home was?\NYou got in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.58,0:47:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, you can't\Nforce them to be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.56,0:47:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The other\Nquestion I had for you is about
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.48,0:47:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,location. You moved here from New York,\Nand are there different
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.48,0:47:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,places that are easier for us to work?\NAnd when we're in certain places,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.48,0:48:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nthe job harder?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.60,0:48:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me sometimes it's harder. I'm in Phoenix\Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.40,0:48:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Is what harder? The environment?\NIs the enlightenment harder?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.40,0:48:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The journey more difficult?\NBecause you convert it into
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.40,0:48:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it's gonna be.\NYou convert anything
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.40,0:48:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere to\Nsubserve your overall
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.40,0:48:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,intention.\NYou pass through the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.68,0:48:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,doorways\Nin multiple circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.68,0:48:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, thank you.\NThe rich and the famous, the poor and the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.54,0:48:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,infamous, it's all the same.\NYes? Hi. So, I'm in
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.36,0:48:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the process of surrender\Nfor spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.55,0:49:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution.\NAnd I seem to be
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.55,0:49:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,losing\Nparts of my right side
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.64,0:49:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in the process. Your right thigh?\NSide.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.64,0:49:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Like my right eye, my right\Nhand.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.00,0:49:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They seem to be busy somewhere else.\NSo, I wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.00,0:49:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if you could\Nexplain surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.09,0:49:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm confused on that.\NOr is this just part of the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.09,0:49:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,process? It has to do with the will.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.09,0:49:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All spiritual work\Ncenters on the fulcrum of the will.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.09,0:49:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only by the ascent of the will.\NAnd it's by the ascent of the will
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.09,0:49:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that your karmic\Ndestiny is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.12,0:49:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,set, and the calibrated level of consciousness\Nis set, because the two go together.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.12,0:49:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only by the\Nwill. So, the surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.64,0:49:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is surrender of what? It's\Nsurrender of volition, of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.64,0:49:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,will, and\Ntrying to control. So, the will
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.96,0:50:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,expresses itself in ordinary life.\NIt's trying to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.08,0:50:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And willpower, you know, is very\Nweak. Everybody's tried
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.37,0:50:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,willpower, and so the\Nwill of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.37,0:50:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is relatively weak.\NThe will of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.82,0:50:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at exactly the same level\Nas your personal level.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.98,0:50:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're at 205 and you exert\Nyour will, the power of that will
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.98,0:50:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to be at 205,\Nwhich may tip the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.97,0:50:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The invocation, see,\Nwill with a capital W is the will of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.12,0:50:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,God. And when you surrender\Nto God's
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.16,0:50:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,will, that means you've removed\Nyour own resistance and positionalities
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.16,0:50:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and vanities. Now\Nyou've opened the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.35,0:50:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the spiritual\Nwill, the will of God
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.64,0:50:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as you experience it within,\Ncalibrates at 850. Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.64,0:50:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, 850 will\Nknock just about anything
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.64,0:51:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,off the path.\NSo, the personal will
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.40,0:51:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then is insufficient to overcome\Neven a
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.40,0:51:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,bad habit.\NThe divine will, however, is enormously
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.07,0:51:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful. So, when you invite in\Ndivine will, then be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.07,0:51:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NBe prepared when you invite in divine
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.93,0:51:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,will, because it may\Nsweep people right out of your
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.67,0:51:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,family situation, may sweep you right\Nfrom one part of the country to another, may change
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.67,0:51:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,your health. You may go from wealth\Nto poverty or vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.63,0:51:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is by volition.\NHmm? No, it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.63,0:51:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by volition, it's by the will of God.\NVolition, then, is personal will.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.63,0:51:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say willfulness,\Neven though you purify
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.63,0:51:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it with a spiritual sounding goal,\Nit's still willfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.63,0:51:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's willful\Nto even insist that you're going to be enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.39,0:52:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,right? Who wants to be enlightened?\NThe ego wants to be enlightened, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.68,0:52:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you surrender\Nthen the will to God, and you say
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.74,0:52:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I align myself with\Nthee, O Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.00,0:52:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that I may be thy servant,\Nthat I may fulfill my infinite potential
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.00,0:52:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to thy glory, you know, etc.\NSo, this as a way of being
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.00,0:52:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world now\Ninvites divine will.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.00,0:52:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, as I say, you're about\Nbetter be prepared, because whatever it takes
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.32,0:52:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,throwing you off a cliff to get it,\Nthat's what happens, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.08,0:52:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the 12-step\Nprograms are so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.77,0:52:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You admit that you're powerless,\Nwell, then invoke the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.41,0:52:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,will of God. So you're\Ngetting rid of something that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.41,0:52:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates below 200, or you wouldn't be\Nhaving a problem with addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.41,0:52:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're inviting in the miraculous,\Nas everybody will tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.41,0:53:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not of their own self\Nthey recovered, it was
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.57,0:53:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous.\NSo, early on in your lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.59,0:53:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you calibrated that 90%,\Nonly 90% of the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.59,0:53:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'd say roughly 90% of the people in the\Naudience will reach enlightenment, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.59,0:53:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all destined, but only 90%\Nwill get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.59,0:53:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so...\N10% will stop over at the casino
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.59,0:53:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for a few...\NBut will they
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.59,0:53:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,reach enlightenment at some point?\NAre you worried about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.59,0:53:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NI let God worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.59,0:53:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Just curious.\NIt's just an estimation.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.45,0:53:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say,\Nwe tend to sweep in together,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.52,0:53:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nthat 10%, maybe after a few
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.52,0:53:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophic disasters, will\Nshift, you know. But, you know, enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.52,0:53:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is a great rarity.\NOnly 1 in 10 million
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.93,0:54:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,even think of it as a plausible\Nalternative.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.83,0:54:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, 10 million people\Non the street. What is your main
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.83,0:54:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,ambition in life?\N1 in 10 million will tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.96,0:54:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize God\Nor to become enlightened, or
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.12,0:54:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you know. 1 in 10 million.\NAnd that doesn't mean they're good
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.69,0:54:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,at it, either.\NSo, rare it is to be born a human
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.20,0:54:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to have heard of enlightenment.\NAnd rarest of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.03,0:54:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to be born a human, to have heard\Nit, and then to seek it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.03,0:54:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And...\NThose who call upon me
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.34,0:54:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are dear to me, said Krishna.\NThe 91st Psalm
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.84,0:54:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,says the same thing.\NTo those who place all
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.42,0:55:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,their faith in me,\Nthe miraculous shall be
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.90,0:55:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,spread before them. See?\NThe same thing is said in all
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.64,0:55:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,great religions.\NThose who call upon divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.92,0:55:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender their life\Nto the service of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.96,0:55:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you become dear to divinity.\NAnd divinity looks
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.96,0:55:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,after its own.\NMaybe the 10% is unwilling to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.72,0:55:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They wish to keep it as a function\Nof the personal world. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.74,0:55:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightened will be\Nwhen I want it. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.74,0:55:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightened may be never.\NIs that okay with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.76,0:55:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Me? If I'm God and I say,\Nyou surrender your enlightenment to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.76,0:55:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. Okay.\NAnd it may not happen at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.08,0:55:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay? Absolutely.\NOkay. If it's okay not to become enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.08,0:55:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,now you've earned the right to become enlightened.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.52,0:56:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,May have to repeat the same grade, huh?\NYeah, a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.52,0:56:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's actually\Nmy concern or question, I guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.61,0:56:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is about worry.\NI worry a lot, and it just keeps
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.61,0:56:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,repeating itself over\Nand over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.84,0:56:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've noticed, or I guess I've\Nbecome aware how much I worry
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.84,0:56:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and how much, I guess it's the attractor fields\Nthat I attract to myself, like kind of the chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.84,0:56:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid, or I worry about\Na lot of things, so I think I create
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.84,0:56:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,all this chaos. Okay, so it's basically\Nthe unwillingness to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.84,0:56:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the illusion\Nthat constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.96,0:56:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,working it over in your mind will\Nsomehow solve it or change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.96,0:56:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas the opposite,\Nif you surrender it to God and say, I can't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.96,0:56:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,call the plumber.\NThen you surrender it to the plumber.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.56,0:57:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't hang over on the plumber and tell him which way to pick it.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.02,0:57:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,worrying is a way of thinking\Nthat if you just keep persisting
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.02,0:57:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,on it long enough, you will change the result\Nand gain control of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.31,0:57:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't. You just constantly entertain yourself\Nwith that thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.24,0:57:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of getting hooked into trying to control,\Ntrying to control
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.24,0:57:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the outcome by sort of\Nworrying it and chewing it, chewing it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.24,0:57:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a natural human\Ncharacteristic.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.36,0:57:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a control issue?\NI would think so. Could you let,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.56,0:57:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to, the way really out of it is\Nto picture the worst possible
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.56,0:57:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,scenario. I do that a lot.\NAnd surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.56,0:57:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to do that anymore.\NAnd surrender yourself to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.56,0:57:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And then ask for God, God for help.\NAnd that's, and some of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.56,0:57:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason they don't resolve\Nis that there's karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.56,0:58:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,blockages of why it's\Nhanging out with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.56,0:58:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain problem\Nwill persist and persist and persist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.56,0:58:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes for years.\NAnd then finally, it relents.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.56,0:58:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you pull the little props\Nout from underneath it and then finally
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.56,0:58:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole avalanche collapses.\NBut, because you
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.56,0:58:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,experience it in time,\Nit seems trying, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.56,0:58:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any way\NI can speed it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.68,0:58:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you\Nquit wanting to speed it up, it'll disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.68,0:58:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop resisting suffering.\NChoose to suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.36,0:58:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I love to worry.\NI love the suffering of worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.03,0:58:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the anxiety of worry.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.03,0:58:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to get rid of a thing is by choosing it.\NThe way to experience a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.03,0:58:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is by resisting it.\NSo you only experience that which you resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.03,0:58:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So choose to worry.\NYour problem is you don't worry hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.64,0:59:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up earlier, I want you to sit there\Nand I want you to really, really
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.64,0:59:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,worry. You're doing a\Nhalf-assed Jamba Queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.08,0:59:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you able to eat?\NOh yeah, I eat. You can eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.53,0:59:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then you're not worrying hard enough.\NWhen you're really worried,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.53,0:59:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're sick and you lose your appetite, so\Nyou're not worrying hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.42,0:59:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Worry harder.\NI want you to promise me
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.90,0:59:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're going to worry\Nharder.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.90,0:59:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Harder. Are you going to\Npromise me or not? I want you to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.99,0:59:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,promise me that you're\Ngoing to worry harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.99,0:59:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you do that or not?\NWhat did I say about the will?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.98,1:00:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have to do that?\NI'm asking you, would you please
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.46,1:00:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,worry harder? I'm the doctor.\NYou're the patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.27,1:00:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Alright, you can even worry\Nby the clock. I want you to keep
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.81,1:00:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a diary of your worry time.\NAlright,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.81,1:00:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,worry you can also calibrate on a one to ten\Nlike pain. What's your worry
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.00,1:00:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,at now? Five?\NFour? Six?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.09,1:00:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Four or five. Five out of five.\NOkay. You've got to focus on
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.50,1:00:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,worrying and worry up to about\Na ten. I want you to really agonize
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.50,1:00:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and worry over the damn thing.\NWhen you lose your
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.66,1:00:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,appetite, you know you're at a ten.\NI want you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.43,1:00:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep it up as long as you can do it.\NOkay. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.61,1:00:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious? I am very serious.\NI'm being videotaped.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.61,1:00:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm being\Nvideotaped right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.61,1:01:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.\NI want you to promise
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.68,1:01:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,me you are going to worry hard.\NEarnestly.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.87,1:01:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're holding back.\NIs this a joke?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.87,1:01:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your question. It's your answer.\NIf you're not going to stop worrying about you,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.99,1:01:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,by God, I am.\NI'm really worried about
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.32,1:01:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,this lady.\NShe won't worry harder.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.32,1:01:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm really worried that if you don't worry\Nharder, you're going to be stuck with worrying this.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.32,1:01:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Work harder on worrying.\NI want you to blow off the carbon on the highway.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.44,1:01:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Run a ride up to 90, 95 and don't take\Nyour foot off the exhaust.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.44,1:01:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.\NThat's the way you burn the carbon out of the valves, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.44,1:01:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah.\NGet on the road and run it. Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.44,1:01:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Go for it.\NAnd I've got to go to the diary. Time diary.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.44,1:01:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just keep worrying.\NAnd give me
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.44,1:02:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a one to ten.\NYou disappear that which you choose
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.16,1:02:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and you perpetuate that which you resist.\NDr. Hawkins,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.72,1:02:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to thank you for having\Naccrued the karmas that led you
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.72,1:02:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to stick around.\NI'm doing the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.78,1:02:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm at a point where\NI'm asked to
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.78,1:02:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,listen for the voice for God.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.78,1:02:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm having trouble\Nboth believing that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.32,1:02:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,God has a voice\Nand that I want to hear voices.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.22,1:02:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got\NCossack, we've got Thorothene.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.80,1:03:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay,\Nso it hasn't been revealed to you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.08,1:03:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what the voice of God sounds like.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.11,1:03:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear it?\NI heard that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.15,1:03:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.\NNow do you hear the voice of God?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.24,1:03:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's present.\NAnd all that exists,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.17,1:03:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as it expresses it to you,\Neverything is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.77,1:03:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you see the beauty\Nthat exists in everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.77,1:03:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity reveals itself\Nas exquisite beauty of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.77,1:03:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of God is innate\Nwithin sound as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.60,1:04:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All sound is\Nthe voice of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.25,1:04:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You intuit the presence of God\Nin all that exists, all that speaks,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.25,1:04:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,all that stands,\Nall that falls, all that breathes,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.51,1:04:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all that thinks.\NThere is no other voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.98,1:04:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That one I want to hear.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.19,1:04:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, would you comment\Non the relationship between
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.19,1:04:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibration of art\Nand the calibration of the artist
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.19,1:04:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that created it?\NFor example, I think that you have said
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.19,1:04:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that Rembrandt's paintings calibrate\Nvery high, perhaps 700.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.19,1:04:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Rembrandt calibrate 700?\NNo, I just calibrate the art.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.31,1:05:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, the literary\Nproduct, the writing or the art
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.31,1:05:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of a person will reflect exactly\Ntheir level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.31,1:05:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, it's the same.\NBecause you would have to artificially
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.31,1:05:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,become that which you are not\Nto create something different
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.31,1:05:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to what you are.\NYou have to be sort of a deliberate fake
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.56,1:05:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or something.\NPretend you're stupid when you're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.13,1:05:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to do.\NA lot of things become
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.10,1:05:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,obvious by paradox\Nand humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.10,1:05:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I think paradox and humor.\NEverybody's into piety
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.58,1:05:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and singing hymns\Nand all, but I think
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.58,1:05:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,through humor, paradox,\Nthings become instantly
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.58,1:06:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,aware.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.94,1:06:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, when self-hatred\Narises, how does one
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.20,1:06:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,work with that and accept it?\NHow do you handle it?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.39,1:06:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do you get out of it,\Nfor one thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.46,1:06:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the fun of hating.\NIf hating wasn't enjoyable and fun,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.35,1:06:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,people wouldn't indulge in it.\NThere's a payoff to hating.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.73,1:06:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, you get to feel virtuous\Nthat you're hating evil and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.24,1:06:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what you're hating\Nis perceptions of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.24,1:06:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even know who you are.\NSo any kind of a hatred is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.24,1:06:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of a perception, see?\NYou know, maybe a mistake
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.43,1:07:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or, you know, something.\NSo you're misperceiving it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.80,1:07:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you hate is a perception\Nbecause you don't know what the reality is.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.80,1:07:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you say,\NI hate myself because I'm selfish.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.28,1:07:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the problem is you're not selfish enough.\NShall I practice
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.65,1:07:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,being selfish?\NIf being selfish is what you hate
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.65,1:07:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,about yourself, then be\Nmore selfish.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.55,1:07:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be the epitome of greed\Nand gimme-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.16,1:07:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I want more octopuses.\NYou see, because you're defeated
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.96,1:07:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by paradox, by the alignment\Nof the fallacious and the imaginary
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.96,1:07:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with the true, you know?\NPretty soon you'll laugh at it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.76,1:07:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.44,1:08:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so cute, isn't it?\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.28,1:08:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so nice to come visiting again.\NYes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.28,1:08:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question from\Nyou.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.67,1:08:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You talked about ego death\Nand your ego death.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.67,1:08:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I have a question about\Nego death.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.67,1:08:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,About what?\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.67,1:08:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ego death.\NOh, my ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.67,1:08:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, because reading the books\NI got confused.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.67,1:08:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounded like it died twice.\NThe question is, you talked about
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.67,1:08:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when you were in the pits of hell\Nand you were murdered,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.67,1:08:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but then you also talked about\NRothmans, and they sound similar.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.67,1:08:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The restaurant, Rothmans?\NOh, yeah, Rothmans, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.67,1:08:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Rothmans.\NOh, those were different levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.40,1:08:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See, as you grow up, you know,\Nyou experience
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.40,1:09:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,different levels.\NIt isn't like you go from this
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.43,1:09:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to that as a total completion.\NYou wouldn't be able to handle that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.43,1:09:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The nervous system wouldn't handle it.\NYou move until you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.68,1:09:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as I reported to the group,\Nthe trap of the void.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.68,1:09:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not trap, but the fallout of the void.\NThe void's at 850.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.84,1:09:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's pretty impressive.\NBut it isn't the ultimate way.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.48,1:09:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nat various levels you experience
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.84,1:09:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the flow of the kundalini energy\Nand you experience
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.84,1:09:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the bliss at 600,\Nwhich, if the body moves
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.93,1:09:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or doesn't move or breathes again,\Nit's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.22,1:09:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So each level is what it is\Nand you can't compare levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.22,1:09:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NSo, from the pits of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.37,1:09:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and then that's when your ego died.\NYou surrendered completely.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.37,1:10:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ego death was in that\Nevent.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.13,1:10:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIt was out of the pits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.52,1:10:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you were an atheist before that?\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.12,1:10:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,By an atheist,\Nyou meant you didn't believe in God
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.12,1:10:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and this guy and that guy.\NBut what did you mean by atheism?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.12,1:10:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not an atheist.\NOh, really?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.16,1:10:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But you were meditating, like,\Ntwice a day or something, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.16,1:10:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that was a different time period.\NYou're mixing time periods.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.16,1:10:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget, I've been around\Nclose to 80 years, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.16,1:10:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a period of 10 years of this\Nand 10 years of that, 20 years of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.54,1:10:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,By my age, you can live decades\Nat various levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.54,1:10:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Decades.\NWell, that gives hope to most anyone then.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.54,1:10:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NYou can pull in what has to be
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.54,1:10:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,gone through.\NAll that stands between you and enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.67,1:10:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,now gets summoned up.\NAnd all the lifetimes and all the karmic propensities.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.67,1:11:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And just after you got everything all cleared,\Nyou just undid the negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.67,1:11:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Something in the positive side comes through\Nand this may bring up
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.67,1:11:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,another karmic propensity.\NYou're clearing out the whole stack.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.28,1:11:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What a surprise.\NA little surprise package?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.28,1:11:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it sounded like you were\Nlike you might have been born
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.28,1:11:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,at least.\NOh, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.28,1:11:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you what it was at age 3.\NI came out of nothingness, void,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.28,1:11:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes,\Na pathway of negation.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.28,1:11:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate reality was nothing.\NNothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.28,1:11:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Total voidness.\NAnd I came out of that at age 3.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.20,1:11:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothingness.\NInto the realization of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.20,1:11:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Which was shocking.\NNot pleasing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.55,1:11:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Like coming out of\Nthe safety of
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.90,1:11:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,equanimity and\Nanonymity into somethingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.54,1:12:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As somethingness now.\NYou can stop, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.80,1:12:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a something, then you can also become a nothing.\NSo, out of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.31,1:12:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the void of\Nnon-existence, nothingness
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.31,1:12:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,was the shock of existence.\NJust like you've lived
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.53,1:12:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,forever in a dark cave and\Nsuddenly somebody threw on Klieg lights.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.63,1:12:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was shocking\Nand not pleasant.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.98,1:12:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of that,\Nthere was this physicality
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.98,1:12:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting in the little wagon.\NThe goddamn little body
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.98,1:12:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,went with this deal.\NWhich again was not pleasing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.91,1:12:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No sooner was there\Nthe shocking of awareness of existence
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.28,1:12:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that then its alternative\Ncame up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.12,1:12:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If it had come about that I had\Ncome into beingness and existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.12,1:12:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,then it might have come about\Nhypothetically, theoretically,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.21,1:13:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,at least to not have come into existence.\NAnd therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.21,1:13:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear of non-existence arose.\NIf you picture yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.16,1:13:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as existing,\Nnow it brings up the corollary.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.16,1:13:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, what about non-existence\Nas a possibility?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.26,1:13:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's a falsity.\NBut it's only a falsity at 850.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.41,1:13:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a falsity at 700.\NIt's not your problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.41,1:13:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But at 850, you're now accountable for that.\NTo resolve that duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.69,1:13:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that an explanation? Good.\NIt's really good.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.09,1:13:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It might take me a while.\NYeah, you never know when.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.50,1:13:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the ultimate experience\Nis the absolute allness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.24,1:13:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The allness.\NSo I had to back off from that,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.91,1:13:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,spend almost a lifetime\Nto transcend that error.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.93,1:13:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the ultimate state\Nis one of allness, totality,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.93,1:14:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all inclusiveness,\Nand the most telling
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.96,1:14:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,difference in quality\Nbetween nothingness and allness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.00,1:14:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is in allness,\Nthe presence of the love of God
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.00,1:14:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is overwhelming.\NIn voidness,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.09,1:14:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which is very, very impressive,\Ndon't get me wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.09,1:14:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it is very impressive,\Nit is an ultimate state.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.28,1:14:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And many people conclude that is it.\NExcept, I'd had the experience
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.04,1:14:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier in life of experiencing the presence.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.68,1:14:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the nothingness of voidness,\Nthere was a quality,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.68,1:14:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,an absent, a non-linear quality.\NWhich is the presence of divine love,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.88,1:14:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a meltingness,\Nexquisite,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.55,1:14:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,infinitely powered by virtue\Nof its exquisite nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.58,1:14:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was missing.\NAnd therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.58,1:15:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,one thought remained.\NAnd it took me all the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.21,1:15:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I could summon up over the hours\Nto energize that thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.79,1:15:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And even then to energize\Nbeing attracted to that thought
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.79,1:15:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to back out of the void.\NI managed to attach
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.42,1:15:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a sense of reality\Nto a linearity.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.42,1:15:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A thought.\NI knew that thought was my only way out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.79,1:15:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed a thought to get out of nothingness.\NThere ain't any thoughts in nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.79,1:15:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a problem.\NIf you're looking for what to hang onto,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.20,1:15:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing to hang onto.\NThere was a non-linear volition.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.78,1:15:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The decision\Nto align one's life with God,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.88,1:15:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender it all to divinity,\Nhad brought in
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.91,1:15:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a karmic...\NYes, I see it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.04,1:16:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a karmic consequence of that\Nthat allowed me to have the one thought
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.04,1:16:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for it to still be in the void.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.50,1:16:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very sophisticated question.\NAnd it's one thought that brought you out of hell too.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.04,1:16:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd you didn't go for the void then?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.16,1:16:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that was the opposite direction of the void.\NI could have used the little void there.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.16,1:16:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we have to quit?\NYeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.89,1:16:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be done just in a minute.\NIt always finishes just in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.89,1:16:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, I have two questions.\NOne question is,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.89,1:16:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you mentioned that the consciousness\Nof the world increased
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.89,1:16:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the late 80's to 205.\NAnd last year
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.89,1:16:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to 207.\NAnd the question I had then was
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.89,1:16:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,why do you think that's so?\NCalibrated as so.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.89,1:16:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second question is,\NI've heard that,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.89,1:16:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't know if this is in fact\Ntruth or not truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.89,1:17:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of indigo and crystal children\Ncoming into the consciousness of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.89,1:17:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with the purpose of raising\Nthe world's consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.89,1:17:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWhether that's something that's not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.28,1:17:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not ring true with me.\NOkay, that's what I wanted to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.28,1:17:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Crystal children and indigo children\Nwould have to calibrate way, way up
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.28,1:17:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to be raising the consciousness of all mankind.\NI think what they really mean is that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.28,1:17:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they would have to calibrate\Nthe consciousness of all to see them differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.28,1:17:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, alright.\NAnd thereby raise the consciousness level of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.28,1:17:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think the world,\Nthe consciousness has gone up since the 190's?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.28,1:17:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the province of divinity, you know.\NYou can ask God when you get there,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.28,1:17:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,how come?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.28,1:17:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I think because\Nthe evolution of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.34,1:17:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if we ask\Nby, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.34,1:17:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is it intrinsic\Nthe consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.34,1:18:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to evolve and seek its own source?\NWe have permission to ask
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.92,1:18:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that over there.\NThat is so, it is intrinsic.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.92,1:18:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's intrinsic to the quality of consciousness itself\Nto grow and seek
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.92,1:18:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,its, to return to its source.\NSo we then
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.46,1:18:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,look forward to...\NIt negates any negation.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.49,1:18:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Increasing consciousness over time.\NIt happens of its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.72,1:18:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get swept along with it.\NNobody ever asked an octopus
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.29,1:18:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wants to get smarter.\NNobody even consulted me, he says.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.80,1:18:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever consulted me on the issue.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.03,1:18:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NI teach Reiki.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.09,1:18:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nup until noon today
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.09,1:18:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have listed that as an asset\Nof mine. But some of your
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.09,1:18:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,remarks, which I can't\Nperfectly remember,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.09,1:19:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of threw me.\NAnd so I'm
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.09,1:19:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,wondering what to make of it.\NOh, it isn't discipline.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.09,1:19:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the misuse of the discipline.\NIt doesn't negate the value of discipline.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.09,1:19:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the business\Nof channeling? Because
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.09,1:19:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as I'm told... I already told you what I think.\NYes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.09,1:19:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you how it\Narose. I told you what
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.09,1:19:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the error is. And you have to\Nsort of think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.09,1:19:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Each of those things\Nyou know, is not positive
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.54,1:19:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or negative in itself.\NBecause such things are
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.67,1:19:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a necessary experience as part of\Nspiritual evolution. You know.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.37,1:19:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of spiritual evolution\Nis you sort of get bit by the bug.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.95,1:19:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you start to explore everything.\NYou go to every consciousness festival
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.95,1:19:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and, you know,\Nspiritual bazaar and
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.95,1:19:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,New Age festival.\NAnd it's
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.95,1:20:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,aisle after aisle of exhibits\Nand parades and flashing lights and
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.95,1:20:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,smells and incenses and massages\Nand balancings. And it's
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.17,1:20:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole area to explore.\NThe only thing wrong with exploring it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.43,1:20:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you know what it is unless you check it out?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.49,1:20:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Check it out.\NDo you think though that if she is a
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.49,1:20:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,practicing Reiki, is the intention\Nbehind her to heal that person?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.49,1:20:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course the intention is what gives it the power.\NYou're correct. So it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.49,1:20:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,magic. So, sometimes\Nit gets caught in magic, then it gets
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.49,1:20:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,commercialized, etc.\NI'm really aware of the commercialization
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.49,1:20:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and dislike it enormously.\NBut I was just wondering if this
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.49,1:20:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,was something that I should continue\Ndoing because I see that as being
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.49,1:20:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,giving. Well, it depends on what it means\Nto you and the part it plays in your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.49,1:20:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, another thing, you become\Nenthusiast to various things along the way
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.49,1:20:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you outgrow them. See?\NBut I think the power
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.49,1:20:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of Reiki is the intention.\NThe intense intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.32,1:21:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the energy summoned forth by that\Nintention. You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.39,1:21:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I would take it out of the realm of magic.\NSo, the only trouble with a lot of new age kind of
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.39,1:21:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,things is they really are\Ncontextualized as a certain kind of magic.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.39,1:21:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for me.\NAlright. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.39,1:21:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I was concerned about...\NThe conscious utilization of energies
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.39,1:21:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for a benign purpose. So, the intention\Nis very vigorous.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.00,1:21:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, because I don't support something, it doesn't\Nmean I oppose it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.56,1:21:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I support vanilla, but that doesn't mean\NI'm against chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.56,1:21:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NDo you have any advice for someone who is
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.72,1:21:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,dealing with ADD?\NADD?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.72,1:21:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe in it?\NDo you think it's an impediment to awareness?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.72,1:21:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I've treated hundreds and hundreds of cases.\NWhat is ADD? Attention Deficit Disorder.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.72,1:22:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? Yes.\NIt causes impairment and suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.39,1:22:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Impairment of functioning.\NThis creates a social
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.39,1:22:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,kickback, which may decrease the\Nperson's self-esteem.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.39,1:22:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the net result may be\Nprimarily the loss of self-esteem
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.00,1:22:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't keep up.\NYou're always getting D's.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.03,1:22:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're always putting the dunce hat on.\NYou're always being the imbecile.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.03,1:22:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're always being ridiculed.\NSo the punishment, the punitive reaction of society
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.03,1:22:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to the disorder, unless it's corrected,\Nis often worse than the disorder.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.96,1:22:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, so what if you can't concentrate\Nand you can't read?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.98,1:22:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?\NIn a society in which this is a necessity,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.98,1:22:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,now you're at an impasse.\NI would say if a thing can be cured
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.08,1:22:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,by a simple medication,\NI see no reason why not.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.08,1:22:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The Course in Miracles\Nand everybody else says,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.33,1:22:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all things are physical, mental, and spiritual.\NAnd it's arrogant to deny any one of the three.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.36,1:22:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would say,\Nif you've got ADD, you do all you can
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.62,1:23:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,behaviorally, medically,\Nspiritually.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.13,1:23:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as any other disorder.\NA duodenal ulcer,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.51,1:23:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ADHD, you do the same thing.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.88,1:23:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I take things for something,\Nso what?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.98,1:23:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you, Dr.\NI have to convert styrofoam back into bone.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.00,1:23:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I mean, that requires,\Nyou've got to put something in your nose.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.41,1:23:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it pulls calcium,\Nand it's a wonderment, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.41,1:23:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So you do that, you also pray,\Nand you also be careful.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.57,1:23:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I had a question about,\Nas students on the path to enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.57,1:23:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the responsibility of walking the path\Nas straight as possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.57,1:23:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we're married, we have family,\Nand sometimes we tend to maybe
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.57,1:24:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,fall to the wayside,\Nembroiled in the problems of those loved ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.57,1:24:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And how to,\Nhow do we walk that line?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.57,1:24:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to set it aside and compartmentalize it.\NThis is spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.57,1:24:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is daily life.\NWhat you do is spiritualize your daily life.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.57,1:24:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you're peeling potatoes\Nis being of service
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.57,1:24:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to life in the form of this family, etc.\NSo what you do is spiritualize
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.57,1:24:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,your endeavors, so that you\Ncontextualize them differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.57,1:24:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is spiritual,\Nand this is family, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.57,1:24:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I argue for the sake of my family.\NThat's not spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.57,1:24:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you arguing for the sake of your family?\NBecause you esteem it,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.57,1:24:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are dedicated to its well-being.\NSo spiritualize what you do,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.57,1:24:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and recontextualize it,\Nand you'll see everything you do is spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.57,1:24:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,if you contextualize it in such a way.\NEverything you're doing is karma yoga
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.57,1:24:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of your family.\NOkay, I got that karma yoga part earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.57,1:24:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm making the lunches for my kids,\NI'm making the karma yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.57,1:25:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the maternal was the avenue\Nby which love entered the human domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.57,1:25:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any love before the maternal.\NMales do not love each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.57,1:25:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not early in the game.\NOnly later, only later in evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.57,1:25:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's after the maternal\Nhas already brought forth
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.57,1:25:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,love as a prevailing energy.\NThe first time the man experiences it
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.57,1:25:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is via the mother.\NOkay, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.60,1:25:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.35,1:25:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is in regard to self-inquiry.\NIn your book, you say that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.35,1:25:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the question,\Nhow is it that I am aware
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.35,1:25:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or even know that I exist\Nis a question that would lead you
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.41,1:25:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way to the door,\Nor one of the only questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.41,1:25:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was curious if you could kind of elaborate on that,\Nand if I'm supposed to ask that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.41,1:26:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as kind of like a form of prayer to God,\Nfor God to show me that,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.64,1:26:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,well, it's moving,\NI believe it's better to move from who I am
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.64,1:26:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to what I am.\NRamana Maharshi apparently,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.64,1:26:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I think,\Nfavored that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.64,1:26:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-inquiry?\NWho am I is already self-limiting
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.15,1:26:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because the who is a linearity.\NThe what you are is a quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.47,1:26:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you experience the reality of the self,\Nit is not a who.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.47,1:26:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a what.\NIt is a quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.72,1:26:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pervasive,\Nself-existent quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.85,1:26:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to wonder who,\Nnot who I am,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.07,1:26:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but what am I.\NBecause what is it that asks who am I?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.57,1:26:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NSo you go back to the asker of the question,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.57,1:26:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're already out of the trap of the question.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.57,1:26:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because\Nwhat you are
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.86,1:27:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is not a who, but a what.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.12,1:27:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,With apologies to Ramana.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.34,1:27:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI had a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.34,1:27:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not exactly sure how to format this,\Nbut you had talked about the calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.34,1:27:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the United States being 420.\N421.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.34,1:27:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've also talked about\Nhow in advertising
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.34,1:27:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you project to the audience\Nthat you're trying to communicate with
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.34,1:27:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other countries I know\Nranked at different levels of calibration.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.34,1:27:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that\Nthe United States can calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.34,1:27:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,420,\Nand yet their methodology with dealing with
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.34,1:27:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,not only its own citizens,\Nbut people of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.34,1:27:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a judgment.\NThat's a judgment you're making.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.34,1:28:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your perception.\NYou have no idea what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.20,1:28:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to calibrate\Nthe level of all the members of the cabinet,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.65,1:28:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the supreme court,\Nfederal court, state court, judicial,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.68,1:28:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate the ninth court,\Ncircuit court of appeals,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.64,1:28:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate all the leading people,\Ncalibrate the speaking voices
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.03,1:28:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of politics.\NThen you can lay it out on a map
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.16,1:28:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to see\Nan alignment of how
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.92,1:28:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that prevails.\NBecause each is an expression
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.15,1:28:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of a certain level of consciousness.\NIt's not a matter
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.15,1:28:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of being right or wrong.\NNot a matter of being right or wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.91,1:28:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, though,\Nwhen the President comes to the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.12,1:28:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or when he speaks to his people\Nand the whole level
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.12,1:28:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of the fear level,\Nit seemed like
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.12,1:28:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the way of getting the people\Nbehind him
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.12,1:29:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,was through fear,\Nwhich is a lower calibrated energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.12,1:29:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand what you're saying\Nthat you need to calibrate the individuals.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.12,1:29:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I do understand that.\NWhen he tells you
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.12,1:29:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a reality that threatens your existence,\Nthe fear is
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.32,1:29:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your idea.\NIf you go off the highway, you'll die.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.14,1:29:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I say that to make fear?\NIn fact, that's why we want guardrails.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.14,1:29:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,See,\NI cannot be responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.45,1:29:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for your decision\Nof how you want to emotionally react.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.61,1:29:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not creating fear.\NYou're creating the fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.87,1:29:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How you individually perceive\Nhis message, but he also
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.67,1:29:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,perceives as well.\NThat's because
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.67,1:29:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it's his responsibility.\NThat's why we said
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.53,1:29:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to not know that there was\N500,000
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.53,1:30:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Chinese communist soldiers\Nnorth of the border in Korea
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.53,1:30:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,was a gross\Ndereliction of dirty duty.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.53,1:30:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If I ask you what does that calibrate,\Nyou'll see it's about 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.53,1:30:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You want a surgeon that operates on you\Nat 180?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.14,1:30:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIntegrity means
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.14,1:30:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that you must fulfill the obligation\Nof your office.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.14,1:30:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As a physician, I tell people\Nyou take this, you get better.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.14,1:30:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't take it, you probably get a heart attack and die.\NThat's not to create fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.14,1:30:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just telling them what the facts are.\NMy obligation is
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.36,1:30:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to my role.\NIf you want to be afraid of what I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.90,1:30:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that's your option.\NBut I'm not trying to control
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.32,1:30:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they take it or not\Nwith fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.32,1:30:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not my intention.\NIf I take the medicine, the bones get stronger.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.34,1:30:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't,\Nyou can get what's called
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.60,1:31:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,fracture.\NNo, it's a fracture
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.17,1:31:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Stress fracture, they call it.\NI said,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.17,1:31:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,do I have to put this stuff in my nose\Nand take this crap and all?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.17,1:31:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, well if you don't, you can be walking along\Nand your femur will just go crunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.17,1:31:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well that's inconvenient\Nas all hell when I'm about to get on the bus.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.62,1:31:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really want it to go crunch\Nall by itself out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.62,1:31:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So I take the sniffer.\NBut he's not controlling me with fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.62,1:31:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I\Nunderstand your point.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.62,1:31:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But if somebody,\Nlet's say you calibrated somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.62,1:31:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that's making decisions like that\Nthat affect the rest of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.62,1:31:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and they calibrate at 420, 421,\Nwhatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.62,1:31:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of integrity\Nfor themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.62,1:31:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and where they're calibrating,\Ndon't they have the responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.62,1:31:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to make integrity based\Ndecisions that affect others?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.62,1:31:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever they consider\Ntheir role
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.62,1:32:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and integrity is their role.\NIf you're the mother
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.62,1:32:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the water's contaminated\Nand you tell them you drink that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.72,1:32:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be dysentery and die.\NThat's your role as a mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.58,1:32:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're children\Nand they're your wards
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.77,1:32:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is now your obligation to prevent them\Nfrom drinking the water
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.77,1:32:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,until they're smart enough\Nto not drink it themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.67,1:32:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Also they don't have the strength\Nto protect themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.63,1:32:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So as mother\Nin their behalf.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.63,1:32:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.\NOkay. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.38,1:32:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to read the oath of office.\NAnd I'll tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.34,1:32:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,he took the oath of office.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.77,1:32:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well they don't understand triage.\NTriage you don't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.77,1:33:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,until consciousness level 390.\NAnybody in power is often
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.77,1:33:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,between a rock and a hard place.\NSo he's gonna be
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.93,1:33:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,vilified whichever way he goes.\NIf you don't kill
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.41,1:33:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,480,000\Nor 180,000
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.41,1:33:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever Hiroshima was\N180,000 voluntarily
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.41,1:33:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you're gonna kill\N7 million involuntarily.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.12,1:33:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So the rock and the hard place\Nof Truman
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.12,1:33:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and I calibrated his decision.\NHis decision was at 485.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.12,1:33:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have been in the military\Nto understand triage.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.39,1:33:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll tell you when I was in the fleet\Nif you went over
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.39,1:33:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to get you\NI went over the side
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.70,1:33:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,swept between two ships\Na steel cable almost snapped me in half
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.70,1:33:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it just missed my head\Nit would have beheaded me.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.99,1:34:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Huge force. As this ship went up\Nthe steel cable went like a shot
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.02,1:34:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,like a cannon.\NIt would have cut me right in half.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.52,1:34:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I fell off the buoy\Ninto the Huangpu River.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.68,1:34:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ganges is awful.\NYou fight your way between
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.68,1:34:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the feces and the dead bodies\Nand the current is fantastic
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.68,1:34:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it takes you\Nand here I'm headed for a nest of ships
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.68,1:34:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,destroyers and sudden destroyers\Nfast little ships
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.68,1:34:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway they're smashing\Nagainst each other
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.68,1:34:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,this one is smashing against each other\Nand these huge things are smashing
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.68,1:34:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm floating right for them\Nall 110 pounds
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.93,1:34:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,flailing in the water\Nand to help me
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.73,1:34:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,not only did I get off the buoy\Nbefore it would have cut my head off
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.73,1:34:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the next thing is I'm floating\Nand I got floated right up to the very prow of this ship
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.73,1:35:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,like this\Nthe Huangpu River current is going by
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.80,1:35:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,dead bodies are\Noh sorry going by
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.80,1:35:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to get them off\Nwe need them off
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.80,1:35:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the river now\Nlaughter
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.80,1:35:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what do we got for a mop?\Nanything?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.63,1:35:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,moppity moppity mop\Nwell we become part and parcel of our message don't we
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.78,1:35:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter\NI forgot what I was telling you about that
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.16,1:35:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the water\Nit had to do with karma
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.16,1:35:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nso actually I got hung up there
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.16,1:35:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,like this\Nand they had to come out and rescue me
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.48,1:35:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so I wasn't too great in the navy\Nthey had to rescue me from the top of the mast
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.48,1:35:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because I froze up there with fear\Nthey had me as a deep sea diver
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.48,1:35:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and they put this bell over my head\Nand the minute I got below water
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.48,1:36:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I got hyperventilation\Ncouldn't stop breathing
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.24,1:36:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as a mesomorph I was a failure\NI'll tell you that
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.40,1:36:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much Dr. Hawkins\Nyou honor me and we're all very fortunate
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.40,1:36:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you Susan\Nyou started this lecture saying
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.26,1:36:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to make your life a mudra\Nto be one with the
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.26,1:36:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute field\Nand I realized that
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.45,1:36:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,when this physicality that we call\NDr. Hawkins speaks
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.45,1:36:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and is trying to elucidate\Nthis concept
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.68,1:36:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,very little\Nreference is made to the I
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.70,1:36:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and you speak in a very non-dualistic way\Nwould it
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.08,1:36:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,improve our chances\Nhelp us in any way as a spiritual practice
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.08,1:36:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to\Nspeak this way
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.08,1:36:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and not use the subject predicate form of language\Nwhich is in itself dualistic
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.08,1:36:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought of that\Nyou're correct
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.08,1:37:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I always explain things\Nsort of in the third person
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.08,1:37:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nbecause I would witness the body
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.23,1:37:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,getting up and doing something\Nand ordinarily you would say I
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.23,1:37:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's sort of the detached witness\Nthat you're the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.86,1:37:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of the phenomena\NI never noticed that
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.24,1:37:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's a fact\Nyou don't language it
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.84,1:37:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as a subject predicate\Nfor an object
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.84,1:37:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,like who is this doing that\Nit's more or less I guess
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.84,1:37:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what in language you would call the passive third person\Nor the passive third
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.64,1:37:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in writing I forget what they call it\Nbesides confusing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.21,1:37:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the passive third person\Nisn't that what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.21,1:37:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the passive third person\Nwhere you describe the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.21,1:37:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as the passage of equalities\Nand not necessarily a personal intervention
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.21,1:38:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you would say\Nthat's typical of scientific writing too
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.50,1:38:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,right\Nsulfur were put in
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.50,1:38:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with one sniff of potassium\Nand bright lights evolved
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.50,1:38:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so would it benefit us\Nto do that
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.50,1:38:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought of it\Nas a tool or useful tool
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.69,1:38:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it may well be\Nbecause I kind of surmised that
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.85,1:38:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,from my readings in the past\Nwhat do you suggest
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.85,1:38:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask it now\Nwhat do you suggest
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.77,1:38:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask it now\Nwe got no permission
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.77,1:38:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,one other thing then\Nbelow the level of 200
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.77,1:38:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,they act in concordance\Nwith an attractor field
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.77,1:38:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and have no personal karma\Nand thereby have no personal choice
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.77,1:38:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,then how do they take the leap\Nbeyond 200
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.77,1:38:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps the evolution\Nof the field itself
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.77,1:39:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in other words the fields themselves\Nyou see the progression of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.77,1:39:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so progression\Nconsciousness tends to
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.77,1:39:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,evolve into greater and greater\Ncomplexity and then beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.77,1:39:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,complexity to simplicity\Nto return to its source
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.44,1:39:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it could be the impersonal\Nconsequence of the karma
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.99,1:39:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,there are many ancient references\Nto it they're not my personal experience
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.99,1:39:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so I can't say\Nthe Rig Veda says
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.99,1:39:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that each thing by virtue of what it is\Nsubserves higher life
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.88,1:39:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and by subserving higher life\Nit earns the karmic
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.88,1:39:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,right to become the higher life\Ntherefore
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.11,1:39:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the lower life\Nwhich it surrenders itself
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.48,1:39:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to be eaten by you\Nyou don't see it
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.32,1:39:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but it gives up its life\Nto God
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.54,1:39:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and then\Ncomes forth its human energy
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.85,1:40:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and now has earned the karmic right\Nto eventuate into humanness
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.92,1:40:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nyou might call it
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.43,1:40:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the karma of sacrifice\Neach thing surrenders its life
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.00,1:40:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to support the life\Nbeyond it or above it
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.00,1:40:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and by virtue of that earns the right\Nto become that which is above it
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.00,1:40:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much\Nwe have three minutes left
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.78,1:40:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we got just enough time for the last\Nif we're quick as a wink we'll make it
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.42,1:40:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the book I\Nwrote that being in the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.42,1:40:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the aura of the enlightened teacher\Nhas a karmic imprint
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.42,1:40:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,can you expound a little bit on what that means\Nto the spiritual aspirant
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.61,1:40:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a frequency\Nthat's transmitted in the aura
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.61,1:40:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nin going into the state that occurred
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.90,1:41:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime\Nor undoubtedly the consequence of the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.90,1:41:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,picked up prior\Nbecause in walking
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.90,1:41:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,through the final door\Nwhich was terrifying
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.41,1:41:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and agonizing\Nfor a few moments
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.60,1:41:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,there was the knowingness\Nwith absolute certainty
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.83,1:41:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,walk through all fear\Nall fear is illusion
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.17,1:41:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that came as a powerful certainty\Nconcrete knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.17,1:41:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and that\Nenabled the surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.19,1:41:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,where did it come from\Nbecause there's no memory there
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.19,1:41:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,at that level your mind is silent\Nyou think when I get there I'm going to remember it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.70,1:41:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not going to remember it\Nthere's nobody there to remember it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.70,1:41:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no memory you can send forth\Nthere's no thinkingness or thought or mind
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.82,1:41:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness\Nso like the vibration is waiting for you
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.81,1:41:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you need it\Nthe vibration is like an encoded message
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.81,1:42:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the encoding opens up\Nas the knowingness of the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.81,1:42:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore it can only be transmitted\Nby those who have done it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.00,1:42:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to be somebody who has actually\Ndone it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.80,1:42:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see\NI will tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.06,1:42:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when you surrender your life to divinity\Nyou will die
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.67,1:42:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and be born\Nthat's a fact
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.53,1:42:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will die\Nit's the only death you can experience
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.48,1:42:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and those are the doors that open\Nwhat is beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.48,1:42:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is beyond all description\Nso the knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.20,1:42:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,having heard it as the frequency\Nand the vibration is now recorded
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.20,1:42:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the field of consciousness forever\Nlikewise am I responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.84,1:42:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically for having said it\Nand it's only with full awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.22,1:43:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that I even say it\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.82,1:43:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all\NI'd like to say I have tremendous
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.27,1:43:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,gratitude for the\Nspiritual guidance and awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.68,1:43:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that your consciousness brings to us\Nthrough your books
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.68,1:43:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just amazing\Nbut my question has to do with health
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.68,1:43:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know you've written that historically\Nyou had a plethora of health problems
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.68,1:43:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that you went through\Nand I'm struggling
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.68,1:43:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with a few things myself\Nthey come and they go
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.68,1:43:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,spent many thousands of dollars\Nand still have it
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.68,1:43:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,still stuck with it\Nsomehow I'm myself in this conundrum
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.68,1:43:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,don't quite know how to get myself out\Nof it
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.68,1:43:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how much money you spend on it\Nit still goes its merry way
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.68,1:43:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of dollars\NI'm making doctors, chiropractors, acupuncturists
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.68,1:44:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a bunch of people rich\Nand I'm still struggling
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.68,1:44:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really drawn to what you had said\Nwhat do you mean struggle
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.68,1:44:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,why struggle\Nstruggling to feel better I guess
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.06,1:44:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,struggling to feel better\Nstruggling doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.76,1:44:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't seem to be\Nsurrendering
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.47,1:44:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to resist\Nthat means you're holding out against it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.03,1:44:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be my quick read\Nyou can go through surgery
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.52,1:44:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,without anesthesia\Nso long as you don't resist
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.54,1:44:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as you stay on the edge of the razor\Nthe minute you get off the edge of the razor
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.08,1:44:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,agony\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.91,1:45:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I would let go resisting it\Nif the bones turn to styrofoam
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.48,1:45:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and collapse\Nwell then you're a pile of stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.48,1:45:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter\Nin the meantime you do what you can
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.24,1:45:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the practical level\Nso you can keep riding out there
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.65,1:45:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,on the range as long as possible\Nyou know what I'm saying
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.61,1:45:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what else can you do\Nthe ravages of age
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.72,1:45:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what the Buddha said\Nsickness, old age and death
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.10,1:45:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sickness, old age and poverty and death\Nis the karma
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.96,1:45:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of reincarnating\Nas a linearity human
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.96,1:45:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Non the plus side it gives you another
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.96,1:45:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,shot at it\Nlaughter
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.79,1:46:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,okay we got\Nthat's enough
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.04,1:46:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you got another shot at it\Nyou're going down the tubes
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.82,1:46:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,go down the tubes\Nlaughing and whistling
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.17,1:46:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,namaste from Ann Arbor, Michigan\Nmy name's David
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.17,1:46:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm part of David Hawking's study group\Nthat meets every Thursday
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.29,1:46:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,way better than going to church\Nit's growing and we wondered
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.29,1:46:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,if you had any advice for us\Noh Ann Arbor yeah the university area
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.29,1:46:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Fred Sauer started one group\Nand it got too big so now there's another
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.29,1:46:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yeah yeah\Nwell you do the same you do with any
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.29,1:46:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,information of value\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.55,1:46:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if you can calibrate\Ndo that way
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.55,1:46:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you calibrate the energy of\Nthe validity of a teaching
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.55,1:46:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and give it\Nthe attention that that calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.55,1:47:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,deserves\Nif I get that something calibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.71,1:47:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,at 700 or 800 or 900\NI'm probably going to give it more attention and value
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.71,1:47:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,than something at 250 but\Nsomething at 250 may be
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.71,1:47:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,necessary to master before I can move\Nthere so there's no point
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.71,1:47:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in jumping the gun either\NI say take the simplest
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.44,1:47:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,things and practice them until they\Nbecome who you are
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.44,1:47:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the next thing will present itself\Nwhen you see the intrinsic beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.44,1:47:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists you see\Nthe intrinsic quality of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.79,1:47:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that shines forth of all things\Nthe next move opens itself up
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.79,1:47:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to you see\Nbecause you've asked
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.11,1:47:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,God haven't you\Nyou've asked God
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.14,1:47:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all you got to do\Nthey say when you pray for
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.51,1:47:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,rain grab a hole\NI'll make this quick
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.54,1:48:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,could you just say something about the power\Nof forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.18,1:48:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,say something\NI could say a couple
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.18,1:48:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,hours about it what would you like\Nin particular
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.18,1:48:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm an addictions therapist\NI'm an addictions therapist
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.18,1:48:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and in helping\Naddicts forgive themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.18,1:48:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,yes\Ncan you offer any help
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.20,1:48:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in how to help them\Nforgive themselves for what being an addict
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.30,1:48:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or the things they did as an addict\Nor
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.59,1:48:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,if you understand the quality of addiction\Nforgiveness comes about
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.59,1:48:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,just as a consequence of\Nof information
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.91,1:48:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the brain cell will prefer\Nthe substance
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.91,1:48:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you can raise neurons\Ncerebral neurons in a petri dish
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.91,1:48:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and gradually increase\Nthe level of opium in the petri
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.91,1:48:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say it was opium\Neventually those neurons
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.00,1:49:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will become dependent on the presence of that opium\Nand if you begin to withdraw
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.00,1:49:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the opium from the culture media\Nthe neurons will shrink up and die
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.00,1:49:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nthe personal self
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.80,1:49:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,has gotten addicted\Nbut so has the physiologic self
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.80,1:49:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that to me is true addiction\Nwhat people call addiction
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.80,1:49:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just bad habits a lot of it\Nnow true addiction
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.80,1:49:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you're physiologically addicted\Nand you stop the addiction
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.80,1:49:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the person will go into grand malconvulsions\Nand die
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.80,1:49:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so you're not dealing with just a fantasy\Nyou're also dealing with reality
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.69,1:49:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the proven way\Nis via the 12 step program
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.69,1:49:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and forgiveness comes about\Nthrough inner honesty
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.76,1:49:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're taking the steps\Ndoing the 3rd and the 4th and the 5th
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.76,1:50:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and following that up with the 10th step\Nall error comes out of ignorance
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.58,1:50:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the teenage boy who starts to drink\Nfor the excitement
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.68,1:50:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the high being part of it\Nbeing socially acceptable
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.68,1:50:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's valued it's cool\Nyour old fraternity does it
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.68,1:50:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea he was playing with fire\Nhe doesn't realize it until he's hooked
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.32,1:50:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why I say don't play with the devil\Nbecause he's been at it
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.32,1:50:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,longer than you've been alive\Nand the built in temptations
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.48,1:50:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,are seductive\Nbut it's too late by the time the person discovers that
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.15,1:50:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so forgive them\Nfor they know not what they do
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.15,1:50:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if you said to somebody at 15\Nwould you like to drink
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.15,1:50:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and become a sick dependent alcoholic\Nand have grand malconvulsions
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.15,1:50:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,if you quit they'd all say no\Nthen you have congenital
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.76,1:50:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and ethnic\Nand cultural proclivity
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.76,1:50:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the farther north\Nyour ancestors come from the north pole
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.08,1:50:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater your chance of addiction to alcohol\Nchances if you're
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.65,1:51:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,from Alaska\NEskimo tribes
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.65,1:51:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Native Americans that live near the north pole\Nthe likelihood of drinking
Dialogue: 0,1:51:07.65,1:51:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and not becoming addicted\Nis practically zero
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.52,1:51:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other hand if your ancestors\Ncome from closer to the equator
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.55,1:51:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the Mediterranean sea\Nthe likelihood of addiction is much less
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.55,1:51:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be Italian\Nand drink wine every day of your life
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.55,1:51:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so addiction\Nseems to be related to latitude
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.06,1:51:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and longitude\Nwhatever it is
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.06,1:51:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,North Pole-ism\NI call it North Pole-ism
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.06,1:51:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so North Pole-ism\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.06,1:51:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,if your grandparents\Nare of Irish extraction
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.06,1:51:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you know right from the beginning\Nin Iceland
Dialogue: 0,1:51:53.75,1:51:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in Iceland I used to\Ntreat a patient from Reykjavik
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.75,1:52:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and he would fly over once a month\Nto see me from Iceland
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.75,1:52:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the addiction there was 50%\N50% of the population
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.91,1:52:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is addicted to alcohol\Nso they have an endemic
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.23,1:52:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,genetic\Ncultural
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.29,1:52:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,so it seems to me\Nthe government and the education system
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.29,1:52:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,should make you aware of that\Nthat you are born to a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.29,1:52:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,genetic strain\Nthat these types of substances
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.29,1:52:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are dangerous for you\Nthank you
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.48,1:52:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you answered a question that I actually didn't ask\Nok thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.48,1:52:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so\Nwe give thanks to the Lord
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.40,1:52:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for thy presence\Nfor thy love
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.50,1:52:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for thy blessing\Nin being here
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.56,1:52:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,each and one of you who is here\Ndoes thereby your presence bless me
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.56,1:52:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby do we\Nbless each other
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.56,1:53:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and dedicate our lives\Nto God
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.56,1:53:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to the pursuit of the divine truth\Nand we do that
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.56,1:53:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all together\Nwe have come in together
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.56,1:53:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and we tend\Nlike swooping in birds
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.63,1:53:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,coming in together\Nwe are sort of a cultural unit
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.63,1:53:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and what holds us together is sort of this alignment\Nand although
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.04,1:53:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by the arm we got today\Nwe are going to lose a few
Dialogue: 0,1:53:27.12,1:53:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they can sign up for other venues\Nbut
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.38,1:53:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the propensity of this group is to spread out\Nover time
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.38,1:53:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,over great eons of time\Nand spread the truth of God throughout
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.38,1:54:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole world\NAmen
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.15,1:54:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ok wonderful
